{"schema_version":"1","crate":"elada","version":"1.8.8","id":"ecf765fcea297f2a","name":"EL.Contexts.TLS","qualified_name":"EL.Contexts.TLS","kind":"ada_package","location":{"file":"src/el-contexts-tls.ads","line":26,"column":9},"code":"package EL.Contexts.TLS","documentation":{"description":"== EL TLS Context ==\nThe <tt>TLS_Context</tt> type defines an expression context that associates itself to\na per-thread context information.  By declaring a variable with this type, the expression\ncontext is associated with the current thread and it can be retrieved at any time by using the\n<tt>Current</tt> function.  As soon as the variable is finalized, the current thread context\nis updated.\n\nThe expression context may be declared as follows:\n\n   Context : EL.Contexts.TLS.TLS_Context;\n\nAnd at any time, a function or procedure that needs to evaluate an expression can use it:\n\n  Expr : EL.Expressions.Expression;\n  ...\n  Value : Util.Beans.Objects.Object := Expr.Get_Value (EL.Contexts.TLS.Current.all);"},"tagged_types":[{"id":"f7994d547409de64","name":"TLS_Context","qualified_name":"EL.Contexts.TLS.TLS_Context","kind":"ada_tagged_type","location":{"file":"src/el-contexts-tls.ads","line":32,"column":9},"code":"type TLS_Context is new EL.Contexts.Default.Default_Context with private;","parent_type":{"qualified_name":"EL.Contexts.Default.Default_Context","id":"49b6caef1350051d","unit":"el-contexts-default"},"dispatching_overridden":[{"qualified_name":"EL.Contexts.TLS.Finalize","id":"11f17601464e3f50","unit":"el-contexts-tls"},{"qualified_name":"EL.Contexts.TLS.Initialize","id":"2b10822053d56957","unit":"el-contexts-tls"}],"dispatching_inherited":[{"qualified_name":"Ada.Finalization.Adjust","id":"aefc22b708595935"},{"qualified_name":"EL.Contexts.Default.Get_Function_Mapper","id":"cd39fc40efaa0fb6","unit":"el-contexts-default"},{"qualified_name":"EL.Contexts.Default.Get_Resolver","id":"f75d39021337bd23","unit":"el-contexts-default"},{"qualified_name":"EL.Contexts.Defaul